        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 5:19PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 519 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Dillon, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dillon, Twin Bridges, Silver Star, Melrose, and Glen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
